<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.242651>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25 – 28. Comparison of structural characters of Pilostenaspis and Stenaspis: 25, 26: Pilostenaspis copei (female), 25 a, 25 b, 25 c: vertex, prothorax and elytra, respectively, coarsely and contiguously punctate; 26 a: prosternal intercoxal process protuberant; 26 b: mesosternal intercoxal process protuberant or subtuberculiform. 27, 28: Stenaspis castaneipennis Dupont (male), 27: dorsum glabrate; 28 a: prosternal intercoxal process protuberant, ridged between coxae, and vertical behind." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/242651/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

